Former Vice President Atiku Abubakar has expressed confidence in winning the presidential ticket of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) ahead of the 2023 elections. He also declared that he came to see his boss after meeting with former President Olusegun Obasanjo in a closed-door meeting at the latter’s residence. Atiku, while speaking to the press after the meeting, also challenged Nigerian youths to compete with the elders if they want to rule the nation. Leke Ogunsola: Group Defends Gbenga Daniel Over Police Security… Sowore To Make Presidential Declaration Next Week He said, “Let the youth compete. It is competition. It’s a democracy.” He revealed that he would declare his 2023 ambition to contest soon. Atiku also expressed confidence that he would win the presidential ticket of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP), asking, “Have I ever failed to win the ticket?” “I came to meet my boss. We will let you know when I’ll declare, we will give a formal announcement,” he stated.